The ps stands for process status and it is a handy tool used to retrieve 
the information about currently running processes on Linux or BSD systems. 
This cheatsheet collets the most useful ps invocations

Show all processes
--> ps aux

Show all processes with threads in tree mode
--> ps -AlFH

Show all processes including commandline arguments
--> ps -AFl

Show list of processes owned by a specific user
--> ps -U user -u user u

Show information for a particular process
--> ps -p pid
--> ps uax | grep process_name

Get top 5 processes by CPU usage
--> ps auxf | sort -nr -k 3 | head -5

Get top 5 processes by memory usage
--> ps auxf | sort -nr -k 4 | head -5
